{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17480280","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17480280"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T23:40:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T23:40:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"33"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"33","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/33"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.23,0.13,0.15,0.33,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"33"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108598"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"33","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/33"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"33"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90967"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"21"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"111"},{"type":"tags","id":"244"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5771"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5032"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5033"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14499"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38449"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38457"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108598","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/108598"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 80-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with a 12 hour history of rapid onset, diffuse and worsening abdominal pain. She has never had pain of such intensity before. Her medical history includes hypertension for which she takes perindopril. She had an abdominal hysterectomy at the age of 50. She drinks one glass of brandy every night and has never smoked. On examination, she is 178cm tall and weighs 84 kilograms. Her pulse rate is 110/min and irregular, blood pressure 95/70 mmHg, and temperature 37.5C. Her abdomen is rigid on palpation and silent on auscultation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Apart from analgesia, which one of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Laparotomy","Plain abdominal X-ray","Non-contrast CT abdomen","CT angiography","FAST scan"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EUntil proven otherwise, the diagnosis is acute mesenteric ischaemia. If the presentation was less acute and the patient did not have such an obvious and diffuse peritonitis, a case could be made for \u003Cstrong\u003ECT angiography\u003C/strong\u003E, with a view to defining the site of obstruction (typically an embolus at the start of the superior mesenteric artery), followed by possible embolectomy. Whilst a \u003Cstrong\u003ECT scan\u003C/strong\u003E might help confirm this diagnosis, clinical acumen alone should be sufficient given the florid presentation of severe and constant generalised abdominal pain with atrial fibrillation and generalised peritonitis. Even if a CT scan was performed, it would not change the plan of management - this patient has ischaemic gut and requires \u003Cstrong\u003Eurgent surgical intervention\u003C/strong\u003E if anything is going to be salvaged. A CT scan would only delay matters.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhilst a \u003Cstrong\u003EFAST scan\u003C/strong\u003E is frequently performed in the ED in patients with acute abdominal pain, in this case the patient has a generalised peritonitis and an ultrasound probe pressing on the abdomen would cause more pain to the pain and add little, if anything, to what is already known.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["An ischaemic gut requires urgent surgical intervention.","Peritonitis in the presence of suspected acute mesenteric ischaemia demands immediate surgical intervention"],"references":["Tilsed JVT, Casamassima A, Kurihara H, et al. ESTES guidelines: acute mesenteric ischaemia. Eur J Trauma Emerg Surg. 2016; 42:253-270"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90967"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"33"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"90967","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/90967"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-07-12T09:11:00+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-07-12T09:12:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"33"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"108598"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"21","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/21"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb5","name":"Vascular Surgery","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relat